                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1045" type="given" value="STEPHEN"></interp>STEPHEN MATTHEWS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 142.) I received the prisoner from a person who had stopped him—I found this weight on him, and these other five I found at Mrs. Fenton's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350302-name-1046" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1046" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1046" type="surname" value="FENTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-1046" type="given" value="AGNES"></interp>AGNES FENTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a marine-store shop. I bought these five weights of the prisoner, and gave them to the officer—they arc pot metal</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183503020173"></xptr>
               <p>—I gave him 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. a pound for them—they are as useful as new weights to person who use them—we sometimes buy weights—we give 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. a pound for copper—the prisoner said he had found these among some dust, which he was sifting—I knew he worked among the dust—I have bought rags of him before.</p>
